   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Example: The retinal model system\n",
    "\n",
    "In this tutorial, we demonstrate how to load and analyze surface hopping trajectory data for a retinal model system. \n",
    "\n",
    "Our goal is to illustrate a full workflow: importing trajectories, performing essential post-processing, and extracting three key reaction coordinates, which have been identified to comprehensively describe the photoinduced $S_0\\rightarrow~S_1$ relaxation and the *cis/trans*-isomerization around the carbon-carbon double bond:\n",
    "\n",
    "- a **torsion angle** around the central carbon-carbon double bond ($\\varphi_{\\text{C-C=C-C}}$),\n",
    "- the **bond-length alternation (BLA)** of the full chromophore, and\n",
    "- the **out-of-plane movement of the hydrogens (HOOP)** that are connected to the isomerizing C=C bond.\n",
    "\n",
    "By the end of this guide, you will be able to compute these features from trajectory data and use them for mechanistic interpretation or downstream machine-learning applications.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a00fb44f-5ada-4f14-8829-e9f0ef880470",

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0912b9c2-491f-46c2-b07a-b385aa6b7424",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2) Computing Descriptors from Internal Coordinates\n",
    "\n",
    "In the next step, we **flag selected internal coordinates of a molecule**. Flagging identifies which bonds, bond angles, and dihedral angles are considered active for subsequent analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "The flagging procedure returns dictionaries of internal coordinates (keys: `'bonds'`, `'angles'`, and `'dihedrals'`), where only those belonging to a specified substructure are marked as active. Substructures can be defined either by SMARTS patterns or by explicit tuples of atom indices.\n",
    "If no substructure is specified, the entire molecule is flagged, yielding all intrinsic coordinates.\n",
    "\n",
    "In a subsequent step, the resulting dictionaries are passed to the geocalc module, which computes the corresponding geometric properties from XYZ structures along the trajectories.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 2.1) Selecting Internal Coordinates\n",
    "\n",
    "There ate two main strategies to select internal coordinates of interest for further processing:\n",
    "\n",
    "If only specific internal coordinates are required, individual bonds (minimum 2 atoms), bond angles (minimum 3 atoms), or torsion angles (minimum 4 atoms) can be flagged directly using the functions provided in `shnitsel.geo.geomatch`.\n",
    "\n",
    "<details>\n",
    "<summary><strong>Example: flagging C=C double bonds</strong></summary>\n",
    "<br>\n",
    "The following example flags all C=C double bonds in a molecule:\n",
    "<br>\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "from shnitsel.geo.geomatch import flag_bonds\n",
    "d_flag, img = flag_bonds(mol, smarts='C=C', draw=True)\n",
    "```\n",
    "</details>\n",
    "<br>\n",
    "\n",
    "When bonds, bond angles, and torsions of a specific molecular region are of interest, the `shnitsel.geo.geomatch.flag_bats` function can be used. Substructures can be specified either by atom indices or by SMARTS patterns.\n",
    "\n",
    "<details>\n",
    "<summary><strong>Example: Flagging bonds, angles and torsions</strong></summary>\n",
    "<br>\n",
    "Example for flagging the torsion angle around the central C=C double bond using only carbon atoms, using a tuple of atom indices:\n",
    "<br>\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "from shnitsel.geo.geomatch import flag_bats\n",
    "idxs_phi1 = (3,5,7,9)\n",
    "d_flag, img_flag = flag_bats(mol, t_idxs=idxs_phi1, draw=True)\n",
    "```\n",
    "<br>\n",
    "Same as above, using SMARTS:\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "from shnitsel.geo.geomatch import flag_bats\n",
    "smarts_phi1 = '[#6;D3]C=C[#6;D3]'\n",
    "d_flag, img_flag = flag_bats(mol, smarts=smarts_phi1, draw=True)\n",
    "```\n",
    "</details>\n",
    "<br>\n",
    "\n",
    "In the following, we employ the `flag_bats_multiple` function, to account for the three geometric features of interest. These include:\n",
    "\n",
    "- a **torsion angle** around the central carbon-carbon double bond ($\\varphi_{\\text{C-C=C-C}}$),\n",
    "- the **bond-length alternation (BLA)** of the full chromophore, and\n",
    "- the **out-of-plane movement of the hydrogens (HOOP)** that are connected to the isomerizing C=C bond\n",
    "\n",
    "These features are defined by flagging the central CC=CC and corresponding HC=CH torsion angles, as well as the chromophore with alternating single and double bonds, using three distinct SMARTS patterns."
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "## 2.2) Computing the Descriptors\n",
    "\n",
    "After flagging the relevant internal coordinates, the corresponding geometric descriptors (bond lengths, bond angles, and torsion angles) are computed directly from the molecular geometries.\n",
    "\n",
    "The values are obtained using the functions provided in `shnitsel.geo.geocalc`, with the previously generated flag dictionaries defining which internal coordinates are evaluated. This separation of coordinate selection and value computation enables a flexible and modular workflow."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "9bfdd2a4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Help on module shnitsel.geo.geocalc in shnitsel.geo:\n",
      "\n",
      "NAME\n",
      "    shnitsel.geo.geocalc\n",
      "\n",
      "DESCRIPTION\n",
      "    This module will contain two types of closely-related functionality:\n",
      "    - generic geometry functions\n",
      "    - functions that use RDKit to identify internal coordinates, and then the above to calculate the values\n",
      "    Currently, the first category of function is found under postprocess\n",
      "\n",
      "FUNCTIONS\n",
      "    get_bats(atXYZ: Union[shnitsel.data.dataset_containers.trajectory.Trajectory, shnitsel.data.dataset_containers.frames.Frames, shnitsel.data.tree.node.TreeNode[Any, shnitsel.data.dataset_containers.trajectory.Trajectory | shnitsel.data.dataset_containers.frames.Frames], xarray.core.dataarray.DataArray], structure_selection: shnitsel.filtering.structure_selection.StructureSelection | None = None, default_features: Sequence[Literal['atoms', 'bonds', 'angles', 'dihedrals', 'pyramids']] = ['bonds', 'angles', 'dihedrals'], signed: bool = False, deg: Union[bool, Literal['trig']] = True) -> xarray.core.dataarray.DataArray | shnitsel.data.tree.node.TreeNode[DataArray]\n",
      "        Get bond lengths, angles and torsions/dihedrals.\n",
      "\n",
      "        Parameters\n",
      "        ----------\n",
      "        atXYZ : Trajectory | Frames | TreeNode[Any, Trajectory | Frames] | AtXYZ\n",
      "            The positional data of atoms to use.\n",
      "        structure_selection: StructureSelection, optional\n",
      "            A feature selection to use. Can specify which features (positions, distances,\n",
      "            angles, torsions or pyramidalizations) to include in the result.\n",
      "            If not set, will be initialized to a default selection of all molecule-internal features\n",
      "            as specified by the structure in the first frame of `atXYZ` and the features\n",
      "            listed in `default_features`.\n",
      "        default_features : Sequence[FeatureLevelType], optional\n",
      "            If no `structure_selection` object is provided, will select all features of these levels\n",
      "            within the structure encoded in `atXYZ`.\n",
      "            Options are\n",
      "            - `atoms` for positional data,\n",
      "            - `bonds` for distances between pairs of atoms (defaults to only bonds)\n",
      "            - `angles` for angles between pairs of bonds between atoms.\n",
      "            - `dihedrals` for torsion angles of bonds\n",
      "            - `pyramids` for pyramidalization angles in the molecule.\n",
      "            Defaults to using bonds, angles and dihedrals/torsions.\n",
      "        signed: bool, optional\n",
      "            Whether to distinguish between clockwise and anticlockwise rotation,\n",
      "            when returning angles as opposed to cosine & sine values;\n",
      "            by default, do not distinguish.\n",
      "            NB. This applies only to the dihedrals, not to the three-center angles.\n",
      "            The latter are always unsigned.\n",
      "        deg : bool or Literal['trig'], optional\n",
      "            If True (the default), returns angles in degrees.\n",
      "            If False, returns angles in radians.\n",
      "            If set to 'trig' returns sines and cosines;\n",
      "\n",
      "        Returns\n",
      "        -------\n",
      "        xr.DataArray | TreeNode[Any, xr.DataArray]\n",
      "            An :py:class:`xarray.DataArray` containing bond lengths, angles and tensions.\n",
      "\n",
      "        Examples\n",
      "        --------\n",
      "            >>> import shnitsel as st\n",
      "            >>> from shnitsel.core import geom\n",
      "            >>> frames = st.open_frames('/tmp/A03_filtered.nc')\n",
      "            >>> geom.get_bats(frames['atXYZ'])\n",
      "\n",
      "DATA\n",
      "    FeatureLevelType = typing.Literal['atoms', 'bonds', 'angles', 'dihedra...\n",
      "    Literal = typing.Literal\n",
      "        Special typing form to define literal types (a.k.a. value types).\n",
      "\n",
      "        This form can be used to indicate to type checkers that the corresponding\n",
      "        variable or function parameter has a value equivalent to the provided\n",
      "        literal (or one of several literals)::\n",
      "\n",
      "            def validate_simple(data: Any) -> Literal[True]:  # always returns True\n",
      "                ...\n",
      "\n",
      "            MODE = Literal['r', 'rb', 'w', 'wb']\n",
      "            def open_helper(file: str, mode: MODE) -> str:\n",
      "                ...\n",
      "\n",
      "            open_helper('/some/path', 'r')  # Passes type check\n",
      "            open_helper('/other/path', 'typo')  # Error in type checker\n",
      "\n",
      "        Literal[...] cannot be subclassed. At runtime, an arbitrary value\n",
      "        is allowed as type argument to Literal[...], but type checkers may\n",
      "        impose restrictions.\n",
      "\n",
      "    Sequence = typing.Sequence\n",
      "        A generic version of collections.abc.Sequence.\n",
      "\n",
      "FILE\n",
      "    /home/tpadmin/git/shnitsel-tools-official/shnitsel/geo/geocalc.py\n",

   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "d25b2535-6cdb-4a53-bf89-5cbe9a5d6b82",

   "source": [
    "from shnitsel.geo.geocalc import get_dihedrals, get_max_chromophor_BLA\n",
    "\n",
    "# compute tagged torsion angles\n",
    "arr_phi1 = ds.atXYZ.st.get_dihedrals(phi1_selection, signed=False).values.reshape(-1)\n",
    "arr_phi2 = ds.atXYZ.st.get_dihedrals(phi2_selection, signed=False).values.reshape(-1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# compute HOOP by subtracting phi2 from phi1 for every data point\n",
    "arr_hoop = arr_phi1 - arr_phi2\n",
    "\n",
    "# compute BLA for tagged chromophor\n",
    "arr_bla = get_max_chromophor_BLA(ds.atXYZ, bla_selection).values.reshape(-1)"
   ]
  },

       "\tconst id_el = document.getElementById(root_id)\n",
       "\tif (id_el.children.length && id_el.children[0].hasAttribute('data-root-id')) {\n",
       "\t  const root_el = id_el.children[0]\n",
       "\t  root_el.id = root_el.id + '-rendered'\n",
       "\t  for (const child of root_el.children) {\n",
       "            // Ensure JupyterLab does not capture keyboard shortcuts\n",
       "            // see: https://jupyterlab.readthedocs.io/en/4.1.x/extension/notebook.html#keyboard-interaction-model\n",
       "\t    child.setAttribute('data-lm-suppress-shortcuts', 'true')\n",
       "\t  }\n",
       "\t}\n",
       "      }\n",
       "    }\n",
       "  }\n",
       "  function get_bokeh(root) {\n",
       "    if (root.Bokeh === undefined) {\n",
       "      return null\n",
       "    } else if (root.Bokeh.version !== version) {\n",
       "      if (root.Bokeh.versions === undefined || !root.Bokeh.versions.has(version)) {\n",
       "\treturn null\n",
       "      }\n",
       "      return root.Bokeh.versions.get(version);\n",
       "    } else if (root.Bokeh.version === version) {\n",
       "      return root.Bokeh\n",
       "    }\n",
       "    return null\n",
       "  }\n",
       "  function is_loaded(root) {\n",
       "    var Bokeh = get_bokeh(root)\n",
       "    return (Bokeh != null && Bokeh.Panel !== undefined)\n",
       "  }\n",
       "  if (is_loaded(root)) {\n",
       "    embed_document(root);\n",
       "  } else {\n",
       "    var attempts = 0;\n",
       "    var timer = setInterval(function(root) {\n",
       "      if (is_loaded(root)) {\n",
       "        clearInterval(timer);\n",
       "        embed_document(root);\n",
       "      } else if (document.readyState == \"complete\") {\n",
       "        attempts++;\n",
       "        if (attempts > 200) {\n",
       "          clearInterval(timer);\n",
       "\t  var Bokeh = get_bokeh(root)\n",
       "\t  if (Bokeh == null || Bokeh.Panel == null) {\n",
       "            console.warn(\"Panel: ERROR: Unable to run Panel code because Bokeh or Panel library is missing\");\n",
       "\t  } else {\n",
       "\t    console.warn(\"Panel: WARNING: Attempting to render but not all required libraries could be resolved.\")\n",
       "\t    embed_document(root)\n",
       "\t  }\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      }\n",
       "    }, 25, root)\n",
       "  }\n",
       "})(window);</script>"

       "    var Bokeh = get_bokeh(root)\n",
       "    await Bokeh.embed.embed_items_notebook(docs_json, render_items);\n",
       "    for (const render_item of render_items) {\n",
       "      for (const root_id of render_item.root_ids) {\n",
       "\tconst id_el = document.getElementById(root_id)\n",
       "\tif (id_el.children.length && id_el.children[0].hasAttribute('data-root-id')) {\n",
       "\t  const root_el = id_el.children[0]\n",
       "\t  root_el.id = root_el.id + '-rendered'\n",
       "\t  for (const child of root_el.children) {\n",
       "            // Ensure JupyterLab does not capture keyboard shortcuts\n",
       "            // see: https://jupyterlab.readthedocs.io/en/4.1.x/extension/notebook.html#keyboard-interaction-model\n",
       "\t    child.setAttribute('data-lm-suppress-shortcuts', 'true')\n",
       "\t  }\n",
       "\t}\n",
       "      }\n",
       "    }\n",
       "  }\n",
       "  function get_bokeh(root) {\n",
       "    if (root.Bokeh === undefined) {\n",
       "      return null\n",
       "    } else if (root.Bokeh.version !== version) {\n",
       "      if (root.Bokeh.versions === undefined || !root.Bokeh.versions.has(version)) {\n",
       "\treturn null\n",
       "      }\n",
       "      return root.Bokeh.versions.get(version);\n",
       "    } else if (root.Bokeh.version === version) {\n",
       "      return root.Bokeh\n",
       "    }\n",
       "    return null\n",
       "  }\n",
       "  function is_loaded(root) {\n",
       "    var Bokeh = get_bokeh(root)\n",
       "    return (Bokeh != null && Bokeh.Panel !== undefined)\n",
       "  }\n",
       "  if (is_loaded(root)) {\n",
       "    embed_document(root);\n",
       "  } else {\n",
       "    var attempts = 0;\n",
       "    var timer = setInterval(function(root) {\n",
       "      if (is_loaded(root)) {\n",
       "        clearInterval(timer);\n",
       "        embed_document(root);\n",
       "      } else if (document.readyState == \"complete\") {\n",
       "        attempts++;\n",
       "        if (attempts > 200) {\n",
       "          clearInterval(timer);\n",
       "\t  var Bokeh = get_bokeh(root)\n",
       "\t  if (Bokeh == null || Bokeh.Panel == null) {\n",
       "            console.warn(\"Panel: ERROR: Unable to run Panel code because Bokeh or Panel library is missing\");\n",
       "\t  } else {\n",
       "\t    console.warn(\"Panel: WARNING: Attempting to render but not all required libraries could be resolved.\")\n",
       "\t    embed_document(root)\n",
       "\t  }\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      }\n",
       "    }, 25, root)\n",
       "  }\n",
       "})(window);</script>"

       "    return\n",

       "  async function embed_document(root) {\n",
       "    var Bokeh = get_bokeh(root)\n",
       "    await Bokeh.embed.embed_items_notebook(docs_json, render_items);\n",
       "    for (const render_item of render_items) {\n",
       "      for (const root_id of render_item.root_ids) {\n",
       "\tconst id_el = document.getElementById(root_id)\n",
       "\tif (id_el.children.length && id_el.children[0].hasAttribute('data-root-id')) {\n",
       "\t  const root_el = id_el.children[0]\n",
       "\t  root_el.id = root_el.id + '-rendered'\n",
       "\t  for (const child of root_el.children) {\n",
       "            // Ensure JupyterLab does not capture keyboard shortcuts\n",
       "            // see: https://jupyterlab.readthedocs.io/en/4.1.x/extension/notebook.html#keyboard-interaction-model\n",
       "\t    child.setAttribute('data-lm-suppress-shortcuts', 'true')\n",
       "\t  }\n",
       "\t}\n",
       "      }\n",
       "    }\n",
       "  }\n",
       "  function get_bokeh(root) {\n",
       "    if (root.Bokeh === undefined) {\n",
       "      return null\n",
       "    } else if (root.Bokeh.version !== version) {\n",
       "      if (root.Bokeh.versions === undefined || !root.Bokeh.versions.has(version)) {\n",
       "\treturn null\n",
       "      }\n",
       "      return root.Bokeh.versions.get(version);\n",
       "    } else if (root.Bokeh.version === version) {\n",
       "      return root.Bokeh\n",
       "    }\n",
       "    return null\n",
       "  }\n",
       "  function is_loaded(root) {\n",
       "    var Bokeh = get_bokeh(root)\n",
       "    return (Bokeh != null && Bokeh.Panel !== undefined)\n",
       "  }\n",
       "  if (is_loaded(root)) {\n",
       "    embed_document(root);\n",
       "  } else {\n",
       "    var attempts = 0;\n",
       "    var timer = setInterval(function(root) {\n",
       "      if (is_loaded(root)) {\n",
       "        clearInterval(timer);\n",
       "        embed_document(root);\n",
       "      } else if (document.readyState == \"complete\") {\n",
       "        attempts++;\n",
       "        if (attempts > 200) {\n",
       "          clearInterval(timer);\n",
       "\t  var Bokeh = get_bokeh(root)\n",
       "\t  if (Bokeh == null || Bokeh.Panel == null) {\n",

       "\t    embed_document(root)\n",
       "\t  }\n",
       "        }\n",
       "      }\n",
       "    }, 25, root)\n",
